<Layout title="AI Search Audit Methodology | Rank4AI" description="How we test and measure AI search visibility. The 17-section audit methodology behind the Five Signal Model.">
<section class="pt-12 pb-24 reveal">
  <div class="container-narrow">
    <Breadcrumbs items={[
      { label: 'Home', href: '/' },
      { label: 'Research', href: '/research/' },
      { label: 'Methodology' }
    ]} />

    <p class="section-tag">Methodology</p>
    <h1 class="mb-6">Testing Methodology</h1>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Our AI Search Visibility Audit uses a 17-section structured assessment across five signal layers. It tests how AI platforms currently interpret your business, not how they should.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">It does not manipulate AI systems. It observes what AI platforms can currently find, read and understand about a business – and identifies where interpretation is incomplete, inconsistent or absent.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">What We Test</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Six platforms: ChatGPT, Claude, Gemini, Perplexity, Copilot and Google AI. Five signal layers: Identity Clarity, Subject Authority, Meaning Architecture, Ecosystem Validation, Signal Consistency.</p>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Two Scores</h2>
    <div class="card-teal-border mb-4">
      <h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">AI Visibility Score (weighted)</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">A weighted score reflecting the relative importance of each signal layer for your specific business category.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="card-teal-border mb-10">
      <h3 class="!text-base text-teal mb-2">Structural Reference Score (unweighted)</h3>
      <p class="text-sm text-text-muted leading-relaxed">An unweighted score showing raw signal completeness across all 17 sections.</p>
    </div>

    <h2 class="mt-12 mb-4">Limitations</h2>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed mb-5">Inclusion in AI answers cannot be guaranteed. AI systems evolve. Weightings shift. Retrieval varies by phrasing, context, and factors that are not always visible externally. We engineer stability. We do not control platforms.</p>
    <p class="text-[17px] text-text-muted leading-relaxed">The audit never assumes something does not exist simply because it was not detected. AI interpretation is probabilistic, not deterministic.</p>
  </div>

